  "texts": [
    "Despite their far-reaching political and social implications, important AI design choices are being left to Big Tech companies that are more directly incentivized to expand their user base than to expand human knowledge.",
    "Big Tech's response to the consumer value alignment problem is captured by what Open AI's Sam Altman has described as a \"simple\" solution: Let users decide.",
    "Rather than navigate a complex landscape of contested worldviews, AI developers are pioneering a new generation of AI systems that learn from users' feedback to deliver content that aligns with a user's specific style and content preferences.",
    "This design choice absolves developers of the task of deciding which information to prioritize, while users receive content they perceive to be more relevant interesting, thereby enhancing the product's appeal.",
    "The rapid adoption of algorithmic customization (or \"personalization,\" used here interchangeably) is demonstrated by the latest trend of enhancing systems' capacity to remember and adapt."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}